energy.usef.core.model

Enum DocumentStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DocumentStatus>
      • energy.usef.core.model.DocumentStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<DocumentStatus>

    public enum DocumentStatus
extends Enum<DocumentStatus>
    Enumeration of the different statuses for a PlanboardMessage entity.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ACCEPTED
      The planboardMessage gets the status ACCEPTED or REJECTED when the message is received.
      ARCHIVED
      The planboardMessage gets the status ARCHIVED when the message becomes archived.
      DISPUTED 
      EXPIRED
      The planboardMessage gets the status EXPIRED when the message is expired based on the expiration date.
      FINAL
      The planboardMessage gets the status FINAL when the message becomes final.
      OVERDUE 
      PENDING_FLEX_TRADING
      An A-Plan gets the status PENDING_FLEX_TRADING when a Flex Request based on that A-Plan was sent to an aggregator.
      PROCESSED
      The planboardMessage gets the status PROCESSED when the message is processed.
      RECEIVED
      The planboardMessage gets the status DISPUTED when the message is being explicitly disputed by the other participant.
      RECEIVED_EMPTY_OFFER
      The planboardMessage of type FLEX_REQUEST gets RECEIVED_EMPTY_OFFER when there is received an empty flex offer (no ptu data).
      RECEIVED_OFFER
      The planboardMessage of type FLEX_REQUEST gets RECEIVED_OFFER when there is received an valid flex offer (with ptu data).
      REJECTED 
      REVOKED
      The planboardMessage gets the status REVOKED when the message explicitly revoked.
      SENT
      The planboardMessage gets the status SENT when the message is sent.
      TO_BE_RECREATED
      The planboardMessage gets this status when the workflow who created it needs to be invoked again to create it again (for D-Prognosis, for instance).

      • PROCESSED

        public static final DocumentStatus PROCESSED
        The planboardMessage gets the status PROCESSED when the message is processed. For instance, when an offer is processed and is decided to make the offer an order or to reject the offer. When the planboardMessage is processed, it will not be processed again.

      • TO_BE_RECREATED

        public static final DocumentStatus TO_BE_RECREATED
        The planboardMessage gets this status when the workflow who created it needs to be invoked again to create it again (for D-Prognosis, for instance).

      • SENT

        public static final DocumentStatus SENT
        The planboardMessage gets the status SENT when the message is sent. For instance, when an A-Plan is sent.

      • PENDING_FLEX_TRADING

        public static final DocumentStatus PENDING_FLEX_TRADING
        An A-Plan gets the status PENDING_FLEX_TRADING when a Flex Request based on that A-Plan was sent to an aggregator.

      • FINAL

        public static final DocumentStatus FINAL
        The planboardMessage gets the status FINAL when the message becomes final. For instance, when an A-Plan becomes final.

      • ARCHIVED

        public static final DocumentStatus ARCHIVED
        The planboardMessage gets the status ARCHIVED when the message becomes archived. For instance, when an A-Plan is recreated, the original A-Plans becomes archived.

      • RECEIVED_EMPTY_OFFER
